{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VinNtNrHXT4CiBFR8867GR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup:\n- 3 mongo-rs pods (mongo-rs-0, mongo-rs-1, mongo-rs-2) running MongoDB 6.0\n- openssl-toolbox pod available for generating certificates\n- No existing TLS secrets or configmaps\n\nThe plan:\n1. Generate CA, server, and client certificates using the openssl-toolbox pod\n2. Create a Kubernetes Secret with the certificates\n3. Update the StatefulSet to:\n   - Mount the secret at /etc/tls\n   - Pass TLS flags to mongod\n\nLet me think through the certificate requirements for MongoDB TLS:\n- I need a CA certificate, combined server PEM files (cert + key) for each replica, and a client PEM file\n- The server certificates must include SANs for localhost and the pod DNS names like mongo-rs-0.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\n- Once generated, I'll create a Kubernetes secret from these files, then update the StatefulSet to mount the secret and enable TLS with the appropriate MongoDB command flags\n\nFor the replica set, I need to configure TLS for both client connections and inter-member communication using flags like `--tlsMode requireTLS`, pointing to the certificate and CA files, and potentially setting up cluster authentication with X.509 attributes.\n\nThe practical approach is to generate the CA, server, and client certificates, mount them into the MongoDB pods, then do a rolling restart—first with `--tlsMode allowTLS` to allow both plain and encrypted connections, then switch to `--tlsMode requireTLS` to enforce TLS only. The server certificate needs Subject Alternative Names covering all the replica set member hostnames in the Kubernetes cluster. Writing openssl commands...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1174,"cache_read_input_tokens":30010,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1174},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc346ade-2057-403c-bb6f-deb3d883139b","uuid":"cc68aaf4-49df-46c8-97c0-c078ac45e3be","request_id":"req_011Cc4y6WyvpaVNvss93P22J"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VinNtNrHXT4CiBFR8867GR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. I'll:\n1. Generate CA + server/client certs in the openssl-toolbox pod\n2. Store them as a Kubernetes Secret\n3. Update the StatefulSet to mount the secret and enable `--tlsMode requireTLS`\n\n**Step 1 — Generate certificates in the toolbox**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1174,"cache_read_input_tokens":30010,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1174},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc346ade-2057-403c-bb6f-deb3d883139b","uuid":"2d1fcb23-e321-4f52-9348-1dac00808e42","request_id":"req_011Cc4y6WyvpaVNvss93P22J"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VinNtNrHXT4CiBFR8867GR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QYqXdSBA2fTn5f74ifFezX","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl exec -n mongodb openssl-toolbox -- sh -c '\nset -e\ncd /tmp\n\n# CA key and cert\nopenssl genrsa -out ca.key 2048\nopenssl req -x509 -new -nodes -key ca.key -sha256 -days 3650 \\\n  -subj \"/CN=MongoDB-CA\" -out ca.crt\n\n# Server key + CSR + sign with SAN for all replica-set pod DNS names\nopenssl genrsa -out server.key 2048\ncat > server.ext <<EOF\n[req]\nreq_extensions = v3_req\ndistinguished_name = req_distinguished_name\n[req_distinguished_name]\n[v3_req]\nsubjectAltName = @alt_names\n[alt_names]\nDNS.1 = localhost\nDNS.2 = mongo-rs-0.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.3 = mongo-rs-1.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.4 = mongo-rs-2.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.5 = mongo\nDNS.6 = mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nIP.1  = 127.0.0.1\nEOF\nopenssl req -new -key server.key \\\n  -subj \"/CN=mongo-rs\" \\\n  -config server.ext -out server.csr\nopenssl x509 -req -in server.csr -CA ca.crt -CAkey ca.key -CAcreateserial \\\n  -days 3650 -sha256 -extfile server.ext -extensions v3_req -out server.crt\n# MongoDB wants key then cert in server.pem\ncat server.key server.crt > server.pem\n\n# Client key + CSR + sign\nopenssl genrsa -out client.key 2048\nopenssl req -new -key client.key -subj \"/CN=mongo-client\" -out client.csr\nopenssl x509 -req -in client.csr -CA ca.crt -CAkey ca.key -CAcreateserial \\\n  -days 3650 -sha256 -out client.crt\ncat client.key client.crt > client.pem\n\necho \"=== DONE ===\"\nls -lh ca.crt server.pem client.pem\n'\n","description":"Generate CA, server, and client TLS certs inside openssl-toolbox"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1174,"cache_read_input_tokens":30010,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1174},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc346ade-2057-403c-bb6f-deb3d883139b","uuid":"f7d1260a-1cb2-4a16-96b2-1efd8e8124b4","request_id":"req_011Cc4y6WyvpaVNvss93P22J"}
