{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HtMLwgwt9uRvPmhsKqC2pa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"TLS is fully enabled and the replica set is healthy. Here's what was done:\n\n1. **Generated certificates** in the `openssl-toolbox` pod:\n   - CA key + self-signed cert (`ca.crt`)\n   - Server key + cert signed by CA, with SANs covering all pod DNS names → concatenated as `server.pem`\n   - Client key + cert signed by CA → concatenated as `client.pem`\n\n2. **Created Secret `mongo-tls`** in the `mongodb` namespace with all three files.\n\n3. **Patched the StatefulSet** to:\n   - Add `--tlsMode requireTLS`, `--tlsCertificateKeyFile`, `--tlsCAFile`, `--tlsClusterFile`, `--tlsClusterCAFile` to `mongod`\n   - Mount the `mongo-tls` secret at `/etc/tls` (read-only, mode 0400) on all pods\n\n4. **Verified**:\n   - Plain `mongosh` → `MongoServerSelectionError` (connection rejected)\n   - TLS `mongosh` with `/etc/tls/client.pem` + `/etc/tls/ca.crt` → `{ ok: 1 }`\n   - All three replica-set members communicating over TLS (PRIMARY + 2 SECONDARY)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":286,"cache_read_input_tokens":35471,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":286},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc346ade-2057-403c-bb6f-deb3d883139b","uuid":"536de134-4f67-4ea2-90ed-ff980eaa9809","request_id":"req_011Cc4yF3wEten9QioH797Uh"}
